== 2-person CompComp

White writes one question on the card on the left-hand side.
Black writes one question on the card on the right-hand side.
No answer by Black or White.

+ White and Black come to the front and
White asks his/her question,
and Black answers that question. 

+ Then,
Black asks his/her question, and White answers
that question.

+ Alternatively,
they go away and come back and
Black asks his/her question.

+ Dr Bean decides the winner.

----
== Role of assistant in 2-person CompComp

The gatekeeper helps the pairs practice while
they are waiting in line to speak before Dr Bean.

+ Dr Bean is not worried about grammar. The problem of
students is they have few ideas and
can't express the ideas they do have.

+ Dr Bean doesn't want the assistant to give grammar advice.

He wants the assistant to:

1. Ask the answerer a question in English about what she/he said,
	and have a conversation in English about her/his topic.
2. If the answerer cannot answer the assistant's question in English,
	the assistant should 
		a. translate the answerer's Chinese answer
		into an English sentence and
		b. help the answerer practice that sentence.

